<body>
    <h1>Syllogism Practice: 25 Examples with Solutions</h1>
    <p>Below are 25 syllogism examples, each followed by its solution. These examples cover all types of syllogisms.</p>

    <!-- Example 1 -->
    <div class="example">
        <h2>Example 1</h2>
        <strong>Statements:</strong><br>
        1. All dogs are animals.<br>
        2. All animals are living beings.<br><br>
        <strong>Conclusions:</strong><br>
        1. All dogs are living beings.<br>
        2. All living beings are dogs.<br>
        <div class="solution">
            <strong>Solution:</strong><br>
            Conclusion 1: True (Dogs are a subset of animals, which are living beings).<br>
            Conclusion 2: False (Living beings include more than just dogs).
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Example 2 -->
    <div class="example">
        <h2>Example 2</h2>
        <strong>Statements:</strong><br>
        1. Some fruits are apples.<br>
        2. All apples are sweet.<br><br>
        <strong>Conclusions:</strong><br>
        1. Some fruits are sweet.<br>
        2. All fruits are sweet.<br>
        <div class="solution">
            <strong>Solution:</strong><br>
            Conclusion 1: True (Fruits include apples, which are sweet).<br>
            Conclusion 2: False (Not all fruits are apples or sweet).
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Example 3 -->
    <div class="example">
        <h2>Example 3</h2>
        <strong>Statements:</strong><br>
        1. No student is a teacher.<br>
        2. Some teachers are graduates.<br><br>
        <strong>Conclusions:</strong><br>
        1. No student is a graduate.<br>
        2. Some graduates are not students.<br>
        <div class="solution">
            <strong>Solution:</strong><br>
            Conclusion 1: False (No link between students and graduates is stated).<br>
            Conclusion 2: True (Teachers are graduates, and no teacher is a student).
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Example 4 -->
    <div class="example">
        <h2>Example 4</h2>
        <strong>Statements:</strong><br>
        1. All cats are animals.<br>
        2. Some animals are birds.<br><br>
        <strong>Conclusions:</strong><br>
        1. Some cats are birds.<br>
        2. All birds are animals.<br>
        <div class="solution">
            <strong>Solution:</strong><br>
            Conclusion 1: False (No overlap between cats and birds).<br>
            Conclusion 2: True (Birds are included in animals).
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Example 5 -->
    <div class="example">
        <h2>Example 5</h2>
        <strong>Statements:</strong><br>
        1. All pens are tools.<br>
        2. No tool is a toy.<br><br>
        <strong>Conclusions:</strong><br>
        1. No pen is a toy.<br>
        2. Some toys are not tools.<br>
        <div class="solution">
            <strong>Solution:</strong><br>
            Conclusion 1: True (Pens are tools, and tools cannot be toys).<br>
            Conclusion 2: True (Toys are separate from tools).
        </div>
    </div>

    

